ALGORITHM: ORDINARY LEAST SQUARES (OLS)

Step 1 — Load Data
Read the healthcare appointments dataset from CSV.

Step 2 — Data Preprocessing
- Handle missing values
- Select relevant features
- Standardize numerical variables if required

Step 3 — Add Intercept
Add constant term β0 to matrix X.

Step 4 — Estimate Coefficients
Compute: β̂ = (XᵀX)⁻¹ XᵀY

Step 5 — Make Predictions
Ŷ = X β̂

Step 6 — Evaluate Model
Check:
- R²
- Adjusted R²
- p-values
- Residual plots

Step 7 — Decision Rule
If p-value < 0.05, the variable is statistically significant.
